  "text": "Most previous models of Separation Logic (e.g., Ishtiaq and O'Hearn [CITATION_1] ) represent heaps as partial functions that can be combined with an operator like ⊕. Of course, a partial function can be represented as a pair of a domain set and a total function. Similarly, we represent heaps as a footprint plus a Cminor memory; this does not add any particular difficulty to the soundness proofs for our Separation Logic.",
